    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture indicates an increased presence in the U.S. Central Command area of responsibility, with the USS Tripoli (LHA-7) operating in the region. The USS Gerald R. Ford is also deployed, currently in Croatia. Aircraft activity suggests a mix of training, transport, patrol, and ISR missions. The overall assessment is that the U.S. military is maintaining a strong presence in key regions while continuing to conduct routine operations and training exercises. The situation in the Strait of Hormuz remains a concern, with the IRGC setting up a tolled passageway for merchant ships. The U.S. Navy&#39;s &#39;fragility&#39; in terms of its sealift capabilities could potentially impact its ability to maintain a world-class status. Ongoing developments in the South China Sea and the Middle East require continued monitoring.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
